Thanks for the review, Stephan.

The requirement is that I need to do an HTTP POST (with the request data in the body) instead of GET (with the request data in the URL) to fetch the scalar values in tf-scalar-card (which uses tf-line-chart-data-loader which inherits the behavior in question). This happens independently of the datum. 

I agree with you that having both getDataLoadUrl and requestData is redundant. In fact, initially, I wanted to just have requestData and remove getDataLoadUrl, but that resulted in a change in interface that required changing quite a few other depending files; so I was reluctant.

However, if you agree with the new interface, I can amend this PR to do it. Basically, we'll have requestData as the function in data-loader-behavior, and remove getDataLoadUrl. I can then add an external function (in the tf-dashboard-common namespace) like:

function HTTPGetRequestDataFn(datumToUrlFn, requestManager)  {
  return (datum)=>requestManager.request(datumToUrlFn(datum));
}

so that users of the behavior can use it to specify the value of 'requestData' to get the old interface. This change would also decouple the data-loader-behavior from requestManager.

Let me know if you agree.

