emmm, I'm following the `AzureError` in azure-core -- https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-python/blob/28a99a0fab81b336b334fbdf032462bb77e67b36/sdk/core/azure-core/azure/core/exceptions.py#L187-L218

I don't think `__cause__` is mentioned in our guideline: https://azure.github.io/azure-sdk/python_implementation.html#error-handling, so I would assume azure-core as the guideline for error definition. So to me, your question seems to be a guideline-scope one.

btw,  by "this should both populate and be associated with __cause__ instead", do you mean the code being this:
```
class ServiceBusError:
    def __init__(self, ..., error=None, inner_exception=None):
        pass
    def __cause__(self):
        return self.inner_exception
```

